FUN FACT:  The blood, guts and glory, running on E and caffeine. I  L O V E D  I T. This was my world for many years….For several years I worked in the surgery room with equine surgeries. It’s what I went to school for. We did everything from colic surgery to laryngotomies, arthroscopies and every equine surgery you can imagine. 
I then came home to 14 horses to take care of. We had Yearlings, thoroughbreds, quarter horses, brood mares. 

The equestrian world was my world & I loved every minute of it & am certain once I’m settled from traveling so much, we’ll be back to having a couple horses again 🤍  Ft. Equine friendly @fabletics #fableticsPartner

Recap 1 week ago. 
Massive success on the Premier of Fight To survive. 
What’s this show all about ? 
17 strangers or shall we call them “ Survivalist” are thrown in an inhabited island. 

Given no food no water. Each only given  1 unique survival tool. Meanwhile the island only offers 4 resources belonging to only 1 person per resource. • Food • Wood •Water •Shelter

Last person or people on the island to survive 25 days wins either 100K to share or 250K for one person. 

Now it’s time to fight! 
Each tool and resource is worth a grapple/fight 
Whoever wins, TAKES IT. 
Stay tuned tonight as mother natures monsoon season makes her debut. 😈 who wins ?

Streams FREE on the CW app tomorrow. 
Catch it on tonight at 8 pm on @thecw

Pupdate appreciation post but make it whimsical.  We have watched each other grow up. She is my favorite girl & wow am I so lucky to have found her at the pound as a 2 month old puppy.  I was 18 years old, it was the day I moved out of my parents house. 
I had NOTHING only a futon as a bed $750 in my bank account and now a puppy. I didn’t know what I was doing in life, except I was going to college and now had a puppy to look after. Well would you look at us now Leila! Adventuring EVERY WEEK, running mega successful businesses, hiking, diving ( she stays up top captaining our boat ) taking flights to the islands, playing on every beach we sneak you into, in and out of the country. Feeding you raw organic food we make for you monthly. 

My God, I am so thankful we’ve picked each other. I needed you more than you needed me. Cheers to 20 more happy healthy years of adventures & new phases of my life with my pup by my side 🐾 ♥️

📍🇫🇯Deep breath in….. & here we go. 

You see, here’s the deal. 
Living the traditional lifestyle wasn’t ever really appealing to me, ( trust me I’ve tried! ) & it’s taken me years to learn that. 

Since I was a little girl, I chased adventures. 
I mean, Once upon a 4 year old, I ran away from our family beach camp site into the ocean FOR HOURS, my parents had the whole beach, police, family & friends looking for me…. 
Finally that afternoon they found me on a sandbar FAR into the water. 
By some miracle I didn’t drown. 

That was one of the first moment my parents started saying I was feral.. 
“ Esta es Salvaje… “ 

 I remember I used to talk to the ocean, I ran around exploring the mountainsides daily. Collecting lizards and spiders to play with, I played in what we called “ El Monte “.
You couldn’t keep me inside. 

I moved to Florida & realized how big of a culture shock it was. 
There was AC in the houses, carpet & no one really went outside because it was “ Ewl it’s so hot and humid “ 

So for me ? Embarking on this insane Ultimate survival series @thecw on “Fight To Survive”  feels  G O O D. 

Im grateful to have met my big brother @k.kaapana  and the myth, the man, the legend  @jonathankmonroe 

So here we are!  It’s day 13, there’s 12 days left! 

And of the 17 that started, there’s  O N L Y  8  O F  U S  L E F T.

Paying tribute to my speargun 🔱 

• I voy to never take for granted, the power you give me of catching my own food sustainably & selectively. 

• I promise I won’t be one of those “ let’s murk the ocean “  or “ kill everything with a face on it “. like a lot of spearfishermen talk. 

So when my speargun was shipped off to Fiji to as my 1 survival tool on Fight To Survive, it was the perfect.  I was overwhelmed with excitement. 

I am endlessly thankful for the stories I’ll get to share because of spearfishing.

Prepare for post 📺 Fight to Survive episode spam.
• I lost 18 LBS coming out of the game, the irony is in prep for Survivor in 2016, I gained about 19 lbs &  lost NONE when I was voted out, for obvious reasons. 

During “Fight To Survive”, I ate every single day. Husked coconuts, forged for fruits and vegetation, beach nuts, we had fish, clam, coconut crabs x2, BBQ snakes, wild boar, minty termites, it was a diverse diet. 

I had burn marks from starting fires & keeping them alive while it was raining, more bruises than I could count, I can’t lie, I was a little banged up. 
But I was the HAPPIEST. 
I loved every minute of being out there. 

Gained something bigger than I ever expected. Can’t wait to share this week what this experience meant to me.
